Advanced Institutional ManagementSoftware Inc said it has cut its workforce to 53 from 74 andclosed its Atlanta office to cut expenses and improveprofitability.    The company said it is also in the process of reducing itsoffice space in four of its six offices nationwide.    Advanced also said it has named executive vice presidentSteven B. Sheppard chief operating officer.    The company said president and chief executive officerMorris Moliver had been chief operating officer as well. Reuter&#3;